      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SNOW ROAD (7) goes very well over this trip including two wins. Was out of placings last time (23.55) at Geelong in a Mix 6/7, finishing fifth and beaten 12 lengths. Looks the one to beat with even luck. BILLIES RAINBOW (1) is worth forgiving last start after finishing fourth (24.30) in a Rank Limit - Grade 7 at this track over 425m. Form from her last run is proving strong. Has ability and is one of the better chances. CLYDE BALE (4) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at Warragul behind Proud Mary (23.21) in a T3 Grade 6. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Expecting another good run. NERA BULLET (2) has a solid strike rate at this distance.",
